<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id122c820f-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777" identifier="/us/usc/t44/s1713"><num value="1713">§ 1713.</num><heading> Documents to be delivered to the Executive Mansion</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Director of the Government Publishing Office shall deliver to the Executive Mansion two copies of each document, bill, and resolution as soon as printed and ready for distribution.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id122c8210-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777">(<ref href="/us/pl/90/620">Pub. L. 90–620</ref>, <date date="1968-10-22">Oct. 22, 1968</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/82/1281">82 Stat. 1281</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/113/235/dH/tI/s1301/c/1">Pub. L. 113–235, div. H, title I, § 1301(c)(1)</ref>, <date date="2014-12-16">Dec. 16, 2014</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/128/2537">128 Stat. 2537</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id122c8211-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="id122c8212-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on 44 U.S. Code, 1964 ed., § 80 (<ref href="/us/act/1895-01-12/ch23/s88">Jan. 12, 1895, ch. 23, § 88</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/28/622">28 Stat. 622</ref>).</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id122c8213-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id122c8214-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2014—<ref href="/us/pl/113/235">Pub. L. 113–235</ref> substituted “Director of the Government Publishing Office” for “Public Printer”.</p>
</note>
</notes>
